snippet.textDisplay:
In all due respect to all my fellow viewers, I'm just an ordinary individual who doesn't have anything against anyone and I barely comment on anything ever lol!
I really felt like saying this though.. "We can't even imagine the hard work, effort, and passion put into a project like this!!!"
It's so easy for us to criticize because we feel powerful doing so, but the ones behind this song also read our comments and anything negative is just going to feel as bad! 
NO WHERE in the description was there a "VS ALI AZMAT" or "VS ORIGINAL" tag anywhere, they never said anything to compete with the original people behind it, then why such hate?????
Please appreciate the hard work and amazinggggggg stuff done to this new version, the Original version was EPIC and this one is EPIC in its own way!
I just felt like saying this after watching "NOORI'S blog" on his channel, where I saw Ali Noor reading the comments and I could just imagine how he might've felt after such negative comments!
Let's be human, let's have fun and let us appreciate every artist who comes and puts so much effort into something we can enjoy and smile towards.
Thank you =)

snippet.textDisplay:
This song is truly a masterpiece ... BUT... to appreciate it, you need to keep aside the original from your memory and treat this is an entirely different song. 

The biggest sin committed here is not the song but in fact, the use of the name Junoon. Salman Ahmed is not Junoon. He can never be. He is a master composer, true. But never the individual embodiment of Junoon. 

When you read Junoon in the song title, obviously your expectations are set in a different manner. 
And then, when you hear this song. You can't help but feel cheated. Massively cheated. Or rather... like being cheated, looted, having your kidney stolen, and then being sold off to the highest bidder. 

All this hate on Rahat Fateh Ali Khan is not justified. Rewind back to season 1 when he and Ali Azmat took Garaj Baras to an entirely different level. 
This is what Coke Studio is all about. Experimentation. Well, mostly, anyway.
